claim.claim-text:
1. A seat panel assembly for insertion into a vehicle seat, the seat panel assembly comprising:
a seat panel including a recessed portion defining a recessed space;
at least one aperture defined by the recessed portion;
a light assembly operatively connected to the seat panel and selectively actuable to emit light through the at least one aperture;
wherein the at least one aperture defines a light pattern of the light emitted by the light assembly; and
wherein the light pattern at least partially illuminates the recessed space.

2. The seat panel assembly of claim 1, further comprising:
a switch in communication with the light assembly;
wherein the switch is selectively actuable to actuate the light assembly.

6. The seat panel assembly of claim 1, wherein with the seat panel assembly inserted into a mounting surface of a vehicle sear, the seat panel defines a plane extending through the at least one aperture;
wherein the plane is substantially parallel to the mounting surface; and
wherein the light pattern is contained between the plane and the mounting surface.

8. The seat panel assembly of claim 1, further comprising:
a pocket portion at least partially enclosing the recessed space to define a pocket;
wherein the light pattern at least partially illuminates the pocket.

9. A seat panel assembly configured for insertion into a vehicle seat including a rearward side having an opening for receiving the seat panel assembly; the seat panel assembly comprising:
a seat panel including:
an exterior side;
an interior side;
a perimeter portion;
a recessed portion defining a recessed space relative to the perimeter portion;
at least one aperture defined by the recessed portion;

the at least one aperture configured such that a light projected from the interior side to the exterior side of the seat panel illuminates the recessed space.

11. A seat panel assembly configured for insertion into a rearward side of a forward seat assembly of a vehicle including a rearward seat assembly positioned rearward of the forward seat assembly to define a leg space therebetween, the seat panel assembly comprising:
a seat panel defining at least one aperture;
a light assembly selectively actuable to emit light through the at least one aperture;
wherein the at least one aperture defines a light pattern of the light emitted by the light assembly; and
wherein with the seat panel inserted into the forward seat assembly the light pattern is configured to illuminate the leg space.

13. The seat panel of claim 11, wherein the forward seat assembly is attachable to a floor of the vehicle and includes a seat back defining an incline angle relative to the floor;
wherein with the seat panel inserted into the rearward side of the forward seat assembly the light pattern is contained between a plane and the floor of the vehicle;
wherein the plane extends through the at least one aperture and is substantially parallel to the floor.

14. The seat panel of claim 13, wherein the incline angle is a first incline angle;
wherein the seat back is movable between the first incline angle and a second incline angle which is different from the first incline angle; and
wherein with the seat back at the second incline angle the light pattern is contained between the plane and the floor of the vehicle.
